definitions.definition: An ornamental cloth , often embellished with embroidery or jewelry , worn over the chest by women beneath their bodices or by men and women as the central part of an open shirt , blouse , or jacket .
A similar item of mail worn over and protecting the stomach.

main_definition: ( obsolete ) A type of men's waistcoat . [15th–18th c.]
secondary_definitions: ( now chiefly historical ) An ornamental cloth , often embellished with embroidery or jewelry , worn over the chest by women beneath their bodices or by men and women as the central part of an open shirt , blouse , or jacket .
A similar item of mail worn over and protecting the stomach.
